<cocktail>
  <cocktailName>Jambledon</cocktailName>
  <version>1.3</version>
  <imageURL>http://www.danread.net/projects/recipeImages/Jambledon.jpg</imageURL>
  <ingredients>
    
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>
        <measure>6</measure>
        <unit>Whole</unit>
      </quantity>
      <ingredientName>Strawberries</ingredientName>
    </ingredient>
           
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>
        <measure>3</measure>
        <unit>Oz</unit>
      </quantity>
      <ingredientName>Takamaka White Rum</ingredientName>
    </ingredient>
          
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>
        <measure>0.5</measure>
        <unit>Oz</unit>
      </quantity>
      <ingredientName>Honey</ingredientName>
    </ingredient>
          
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>
        <measure>3</measure>
        <unit>Sprigs</unit>
      </quantity>
      <ingredientName>Mint Leaves</ingredientName>
    </ingredient>
    
    <ingredient>
      <quantity>
        <measure>0.5</measure>
        <unit>Cup</unit>
      </quantity>
      <ingredientName>Ice</ingredientName>
    </ingredient>
  </ingredients>
        
  <method>
    Chop up those mint leaves as small as you can. Put everything in a blender until the ice is smoothe and the mint is as finely chopped as possible. Slowly pour it into a tumbler to catch any ice lumps before they fall out, and top with some mint leaves to garnish.
  </method>
  
  <notes>
    Be careful - this is delicious. It's like English summertime took a Carribean vacation.
  </notes>
  
  <owner ownerID = '1'>Dan Read</owner>
</cocktail>
